# This shell scirpt should start the proxy on the target system.
#
# My local version does the following:
#
#  - sets up IPtables
#  - runs pump (a DHCP client)
#  - sets up nsswitch.conf
#  - sets up /etc/host.conf
#  
# and then starts the Erlang code, like this:
/opt/erlang/bin/erl -s reflect go -detached

